textMessage ACCESS_CONTROL_INFO (
    message {
        text:
            ```
            <p>When Access Control is enabled, Administrators have the ability to restrict access to certain application features, for authenticated users. Team Calendar supports the following 3 access levels; Reader, Contributor and Administrator.
              <b>Reader's</b> have read-only access and can also view reports.
              <b>Contributor's</b> can create, edit, delete and view reports.
              <b>Administrator's</b>, in addition to Contributor's capability, can also perform Team Calendar administration, including configuration of access control, exporting and installing or uninstalling sample data.</p> 
            
            ```
        language: en
    }
)

textMessage ACL_DISABLED (
    message {
        text: <p>All users are currently <strong>Administrators</strong>. Please enable Access Control to restrict user access to this application.</p>
        language: en
    }
)

textMessage ACL_ENABLED (
    message {
        text: <p>Only users defined in the Access Control List have access to this application.</p>
        language: en
    }
)

textMessage ACL_PUBLIC_CONTRIBUTE (
    message {
        text: <p>All authenticated users have <strong>Reader</strong> and <strong>Contributor</strong> access.</p><p>Administrators are restricted by the Access Control List.</p>
        language: en
    }
)

textMessage ACL_PUBLIC_READONLY (
    message {
        text: <p>All authenticated users have <strong>Reader</strong> access.</p><p>Contributors and Administrators are restricted by the Access Control List.</p>
        language: en
    }
)

textMessage AC_CONFIGURATION_INFO (
    message {
        text:
            ```
            <p><strong>Enabling Access Control</strong> allows the application and its features to be controlled by the <strong>Access Control List</strong>, as defined by the application administrator. This application has 3 access levels available that can be granted to a user; Administrator, Contributor and Reader. Please see the Manage Access Control List page for further details on what each level provides.</p>
            
            <p>In addition, if you want to make every authenticated user a 'Reader' of your application, you can select Reader access for any authenticated user from the Access Control Scope configuration option. Similarly, selecting Contributor access for any authenticated user will provide contributor access to any user who can authenticate into your application.</p>
            
            <br>
            <p><b>Disabling Access Control</b> means that access to the application and all of its features including Administration are open to any user who can authenticate to the application.</p>
            <br>
            <p>Note: Irrespective of whether Access Control is enabled or disabled, a user still has to authenticate successfully into the application.</p>
            ```
        language: en
    }
)

